**Describe the bug**
We are trying to connect to our socket server via nginx reverse proxy. It is working fine when done using docker-compose on http but doesn't work when tried over https. 

**client(http) -> server(http)   -- `Working`
client(http) -> server(https)   -- `Not working`
client(https) -> server(https)   -- `Not working`**

**To Reproduce**

Socket.IO server version: `4.4.1`

*Server*

```js
const http = require("http")
const io = require("socket.io")(http).of("/mybot-ws");

io.on("connection", (socket) => {
  console.log(`connect ${socket.id}`);

  socket.on("disconnect", () => {
    console.log(`disconnect ${socket.id}`);
  });
});
```


*Nginx*
```
location /path1/path2/path3/ {
    proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_pass https://abc.com/socket.io/;
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
    proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
}
```

Socket.IO client version: `4.4.1`

*Client*

```js
import { io } from "socket.io-client";
  
const socket = io("/mybot-ws", { path: "/path1/path2/path3", transports: ['websocket'] });

socket.on("connect", () => {
  console.log(`connect ${socket.id}`);
});

socket.on("disconnect", () => {
  console.log("disconnect");
});
```

**Expected behavior**
Client and server should be able to connect in the current setup with nginx as a reverse proxy for socket.io

